laboratory_examinations.findings: Interval development of small to moderate bilateral pleural effusions with associated compressive atelectasis. Liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation, no suspicious focal lesion, mild circumferential wall edema of gallbladder. Normal pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and urinary bladder. No free fluid in the pelvis or significant atherosclerotic disease noted. A small fluid collection at the site of the umbilical laparoscopic port (2.7 x 1.7 cm), with no significant associated enhancement.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Interval development of small to moderate bilateral pleural effusions.
